      passage: `Though Middle English was widely spoken in fourteenth-century England, the English language was rarely employed in literature until poet Geoffrey Chaucer pioneered its literary use. _____ his manuscripts contain the first documented uses of over 2,000 English words&mdash;like the word &ldquo;digestion&rdquo; in his 1395 poem &ldquo;The Squire&rsquo;s Tale&rdquo;&mdash;which led a contemporary to dub him &ldquo;the first finder of our fair language.&rdquo;`,
