      passage: `Neoclassical economic models assume that people consistently make rational economic decisions, but Francesca Gino of Harvard Business School makes no such assumption; behavioral economists such as Gino, whose research focuses on worker productivity, _____ that economic decision-making can in fact be highly irrational.`,
      prompt: `Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?`,
